revision.text:
{{DISPLAYTITLE:Sector_SetCurrent}} {{Special|220|tag, amount, angle, useline|Sector|Current}} * ''tag'': Tag of affected sector * ''amount'': Strength of the current * ''angle'': Angle the current flows * ''useline'': Whether to get the strength and angle from the line instead
If ''useline'' is 1, this behaves just like BOOM's 225 linedef. If ''useline'' is 0, then the ''amount'' and ''angle'' parameters are used instead of the size and orientation of the line.
== Examples == {{noexamples}}
== Conversions from linedef types == The following Doom map format types can be converted as Sector_SetCurrent: {| {{prettytable}} !Type!!Conversion!!Trigger |- |{{icon|Boom}} 225:Set Current || Sector_SetCurrent (tag, 0, 0, 1) || |- |{{icon|Eternity}} 294:TransferHereticCurrent || Sector_SetCurrent (tag, 0, 0, 1) || |}
